    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for the discerning driver is a mechanically robust 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2). This example is powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six, putting power to the rear wheels via a tactile G96 6-speed manual transaxle. Enthusiast-critical maintenance is up to date, featuring a ceramic IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced water pump and low-temperature thermostat. The suspension geometry remains precise thanks to Bilstein B6 dampers and refreshed bushings, maintaining the legendary feedback of the hydraulic steering rack. Braking performance is handled by four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors. While the exterior shows minor cosmetic evidence of spirited road use, the drivetrain is dialed-in and the cabin remains a focused environment with firm seat bolsters and crisp instrumentation. A documented service history accompanies this well-sorted driver's car.",
      "price": 36500.0,
